<span id="freeTextContainer16040654000450688358">How deadly can boredom really be? For some it can become deadly enough… <br/>“I should say it was time she began to be bored. They’ve been married five or six years. Quite well off but everything goes in keeping up the house. I’ve never seen it but I’ve an idea it’s huge and quite hideous.”<br/>While endeavouring to escape the boredom of the aristocratic life one may find a lot of troubles on one’s romantic head…<br/><b>Evelyn Waugh</b> is a brilliant observer of human peccadilloes and in <i>A Handful of Dust</i> he is at h</span>
  <span id="freeText16040654000450688358" style="display:none">How deadly can boredom really be? For some it can become deadly enough… <br />“I should say it was time she began to be bored. They’ve been married five or six years. Quite well off but everything goes in keeping up the house. I’ve never seen it but I’ve an idea it’s huge and quite hideous.”<br />While endeavouring to escape the boredom of the aristocratic life one may find a lot of troubles on one’s romantic head…<br /><b>Evelyn Waugh</b> is a brilliant observer of human peccadilloes and in <i>A Handful of Dust</i> he is at his best.</span>
